-CONST--0 year ago , i establish a non @-@ profit organization to work with the NE_ethnic-group-0 , focusing on a variety of aspect ( education , development , etc.), but also on promote awareness of their culture , and to try to preserve it .
in the NE_ethnic-group-0 culture , there be no marriage .
no marriage ceremony exist .
there be no expectation whatsoever of life @-@ time bond or pairings .
children be raise not only without an expectation of spend their life with that -CONST--0 special person , but they often do n't even know ( or care ) ENT_amr-unknown-0 their biological father be .
in the NE_ethnic-group-0 culture , men and women can change and choose partner as they please .
monogamy be not consider special or even particularly desirable .
the NE_ethnic-group-0 live in large extended family , with many generation ( grandparent , parent , children , grandchildren , etc.) all live together in the same house .
men sleep in communal sleep room ( they do n't have private bedroom ) ; only the women have the luxury of a private bedroom .
thus , women tend to the the one in control of relationship .
traditionally , a NE_ethnic-group-0 woman will invite a man to spend the night with her .
the man will come to her home at night , sneak in through her window ( -CONST--0 be also a part of the NE_ethnic-group-0 culture that , while everyone know this be happen , it should be do in a manner that be not obvious ) , spend the night , and then leave early the next morning before everyone wake up .
thus the term " walk marriage "...because the men must walk to and from -CONST--0 assign rendevous each night .
the NE_ethnic-group-0 walk marriage be generally the most interesting -- and misunderstood -- aspect of -CONST--0 culture .
people be always fascinate by it , but misunderstanding and misperceptions abound .
-CONST--0 of the most common misperceptions be that the NE_ethnic-group-0 be very promiscuous , change partner all the time .
that be patently not true ; in fact , many NE_ethnic-group-0 pair will last for ENT_temporal-quantity-0 , and even ENT_temporal-quantity-1 .
there be no social stigma if someone do change partner often , but it be more common for the NE_ethnic-group-0 to engage in what have be describe as " serial monogamy "...that be , they do n't stick with -CONST--0 partner for their whole life , but each pair will tend to last for an extended period , and they won't generally have multiple partner while in a relationship .
however , there be fascinate and very unique aspect of these walk marriage .
ENT_ordinal-entity-0 , even among couple who be together for months/years/decades , they generally will never actually live together , or share property .
the man will continue to live in his family 's home , and his responsibility be to that family ; while the woman will continue to live her her home , and be responsible to her family .
the man will visit her at night , but the rest of the time they generally live separate life .
and what if they have a baby ? in general , father have little or no responsibility for children produce from such union ;
the baby will be raise in the mother 's home , and be a part of her family , not the father 's .
however , that do not mean that the men have no responsibility...it be just that the focus of that responsibility be shift .
in most culture , a man will be responsible to care for his own children ;
in NE_ethnic-group-0 culture , a man be responsible to care for the children of his sisters/nieces/aunts/etc . so NE_ethnic-group-1 men still have full parenting responsibilities...perhaps even moreso , since they may end up share responsibility for the children of many family member .
now , in some case , NE_ethnic-group-0 men do want to be involve in their own childrens ' upbringing .
if that be the case , after the child be born , the father will go to the mother 's home , and present the family matriarch with gift , ask to be accept as the father .
if the matriarch accept him , he be then an ' honorary member ' of the family , and have the right to visit and @/@ or stay there like any other family member , and to help raise the child .
however , this be not a frequent practice .
although this sound very strange at first , it actually provide remarkable stability for the children .
ENT_ordinal-entity-0 , they be not raise by just -CONST--0 parent ; everyone in the family share in parental duty , so the child really end up have multiple father and mother figure .
furthermore , if the mother and father end their relationship , there be virtually no impact or stress for the child .
there 's no fight over split property , because they never share property .
there 's no fight over custody of the child , because the child never belong to the father to begin with .
the mother 's relationship with different men may change , but it have little or no effect on the children .
-CONST--0 more thing i 'd like to point out . while this system actually work very effectively for the NE_ethnic-group-0 , it work only in a situation where there be a large extend family to provide support .
for those NE_ethnic-group-0 men and women who leave home to live @/@ work on their own in other city , they almost always choose more traditional marriage .
